In 2018, Nishinorikura Kofun was Historic site a National {{ill|Historic site|ja|史跡|1=Historic site|lt=Historic site of Japan|12=draft|12=draft}}} as part of the "Somanouchi Kofun Group."<ref name="Notification"/>  

== Mound burial ==  
The mound's area are as follows:{{Sfn|Somanouchi Kofun Group Study|2014}}{{Sfn|Nishinorikura Kofun (Tenri Kofun 100)|2015}}  
* Mound length: Approx. 118 meters  
* Rear circular portion: Possibly two-tiered  
** Diameter: Approx. 66 meters  
** Height: Approx. 15.5 meters  
* Front rectangular portion  
** Width: Approx. 88 meters  
** Height: Approx. 16 meters  

The mound length ranks second within the Somanouchi Kofun Group, following {{ill|Nishiyama Kofun|ja|西山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}. A flat area resembling a base extends approximately 20–30 meters east-west and 130 meters north-south along the western edge of the mound. Excavation suggests that this flat area resulted from the burial of the inner moat and embankment. An outer moat has also been discovered, indicating the potential presence of a double moat system.  

